Human epigenetic enzymes

A list of 212 epigenetic enzymes, including writers, readers, editors and erasers of the most important epigenetic marks.

data(human.ee)

Format

A data frame with 4 columns and 212 rows coorresponding to genes.

Source

Yang Z, Jones A, Widschwendter M, Teschendorff AE. An integrative pan-cancer-wide analysis of epigenetic enzymes reveals universal patterns of epigenomic deregulation in cancer. Genome Biol. 2015 Jul 14;16:140. doi: 10.1186/s13059-015-0699-9.

Examples

 data(human.ee)
 head(human.ee)
